A Parliament was called at Nottingham by King Richard the first, after his return from his Captivity, which Hovedon parte posteriore.


continued but four days; a Parliament in 7. Johannis; 
                  Mat. Paris 247. a great Councel or Parliament was holden at London, and Adjourned to Reading, whither the King not coming at the day appointed, it was three days after Adjourned to Wallingford.
